<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>U.S. and China Will Start Discussing A.I. Safety, Bessent Says</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/14/world/asia/china-us-ai-safety.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/14/world/asia/china-us-ai-safety.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/14/world/asia/china-us-ai-safety.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent did not say when these talks would happen. There are fears in the United States and China about the threats from A.I., but neither side is willing to slow down its development.</description><dc:creator>Vivian Wang</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 03:55:47 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Foreign Policy</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Xi Jinping</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><media:content url="http