ywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cerebras</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Silicon Valley</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/14/multimedia/14biz-cerebras-2-wbqh/14biz-cerebras-2-wbqh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Christie Hemm Klok for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Cerebras presages a series of potential “mega I.P.O.s” from A.I.-related firms including OpenAI, Anthropic and Elon Musk’s SpaceX.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>How Good Is Google’s Gemini AI at Making Travel Plans?</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/30/travel/ai-travel-plan-gemini-vacation.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/30/travel/ai-travel-plan-gemini-vacation.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/04/30/travel/ai-travel-plan-gemini-vacation.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Gemini is a digital Swiss Army knife for planning flights, activities and routes, but it isn’t perfect. Why did it forget to put underwear on the packing list?</description><dc:creator>Brian X. Chen</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 09:01:13 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Travel</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tourism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">vacations</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Service</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">H